Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of Diethyl Carbonate + Toluene, + Methanol, and + 2-Propanol from (293.15 to 363.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities for diethyl carbonate (DEC) with toluene, methanol, and 2-propanol were determined over several temperatures and at atmospheric pressure. The measurements were carried out over the whole mole fraction, using a vibrating-tube densimeter and an Ubbelohde viscometer. Density and viscosity measurements were used to compute the excess molar volumes, V E, and viscosity deviations, centse. The excess molar volumes, V E, and viscosity deviations, centse, have been fitted to Redlich-Kister equation.
